Redescription . Color : Body dark or dark with pale legs and markings on hemelytron ( Figs. 15 , 194, 195 ). Head with pale and brown setae. Anteocular part of head yellowish with darker lateral parts of head (except antennifer) or brown (with pale clypeus). Postocular part of head brown or dark brown. Specimens with brown anteocular part of head, often with paler longitudinal line (from interocular furrow to basal part of clypeus). Scape, basiflagellum (exept base) and intercalar segments yellowish or slightly darker. Pedicel dark brown or brown. pale (rarely in same color as second segment) with slightly darker apical and basal part. Pronotum dark brown often with paler posterior lobe. Lateral parts of posterior pronotal lobe brown paler than medial part. All visible labial segments pale or with darker first visible segment. Some specimens with dark spot on dorsal part of first labial segment. Scutellum dark brown to black or with paler medial part. Hemelytron dark brown with basal part, clavus and claval suture pale (except dark medial part of internal margin) (
S. flaviceps
) ( Fig. 15 ); basal part of hemelytron dark (
S. flaviceps var. lugubris
) ( Fig. 195 ); margin of basal part of hemelytron and basal part of clavus pale (
S. flaviceps var. adelpha
) ( Fig. 194 ), membrane dark, some specimens with distinctly paler posterior pronotal lobe. Apex of membrane whitish. Legs yellowish. Ventral side of thorax dark (in color of anterior pronotal lobe). Abdomen beneath black with pale, longitudinal spot on ventral side or only with pale line (created by pale spots on sternites and with different width). Connexives dark brown or bicolorous with pale latero-apical part. Connexives of seventh segment pale (rarely dark). Pygophore dark with paler apical margin.

Structure
: Body large and robust. Head, pronotum and scutellum shiny. Head with different sized setae and 4 pairs of trichobothrial setae, shlallow apodeme depression and transversal furrow. Dorsal surface of antennifers smooth. Area from base of clypeus to posterior margin of ocelli glabrous. Anteocular part of head 3.33–3.71 times longer than postocular part in females and 4.4–4.5 times in males. Eyes and ocelli large. Eye narrower than synthlipsis with distinct S-shape curvature in lateral view (
Fig. 190
). Scape club-shaped not reaching apex of head, thickened distally with variably-sized (mostly long), erect setae. Pedicel with dense, adherent, short setae and 4 long (
Fig. 170
) trichobothrial setae. Basi- and distiflagellum with short adherent setae and numerous longer, regularly arranged, erect setae. Second labial with enlarged basal part, segment reaching posterior margin of head. Anterior pronotal with distinct sulci and lack of collar. Apodeme depression of APL short and wide. Ridges od proepisternum and proepimeron connected in entire length. Posterior pronotal lobe smooth, slightly flattened in middle, over curvature of transversal suture. Metapleura with two incomplete ridges. Females with delicate depressed, longitudinal line on flattened area. Anterior margin of posterior lobe with dense, longitudinal sculpturations (absent in some specimens). Margins of scutellum strongly thickened and shining with dense different-sized setae (mostly medium-sized). Central part of scutellum with granulations. Apex short, rounded. Tibia and tarsus with spine-like setae (mostly on inner side). All legs with long trichobothrial setae. Coxa with long, dense setae. Corium dull with shining basal part and slightly granulated costal margin. Hemelytron with different-sized setae, dense and rather long on costal margin. Hemelytron surpassing (males) or almost reaching (females) apex of abdomen. Abdomen ventrally with long and dense setae. Spiracles III–IV placed distant from ventral connexival suture.

Genitalia
: Male—Median process of pygophore (
Fig. 19
) with sharp apex (
Fig. 24
). Both parameres slender and triangular in dorsal view with medium sized setae on outer and inner side (
Figs. 20–23
). Pedicel of aedeagus bent laterally (
Fig. 27
) and distinctly curved (
Figs. 25, 26
). Basal lobe of dorsal phallothecal sclerite enlarged on right side with rounded process (
Fig. 25
). Dorsal endosomal sclerite covered by distinct spines (
Fig. 27
).

Female—Valvifer I rounded (
Fig. 18
), on outer side with very dense and short setae and a few distinctly longer setae. Styloids on inner margin with dense, short setae and with sharp apical part. Basal part of styloids with triangular indentation (
Fig. 16
). Basal part of valvula II with process convolute inwards, forked in apical part with two apices, a thin and sharp and a broad and rounded apex respectively. Basal margin irregular in shape (
Fig. 17
).
